# Banh Mi Sandwich
Serves 2

## Ingredients
* 1lb Chicken Breast
* 3 cloves garlic
* 2 tbsp. soy sauce
* 2 tbsp. fish sauce
* 1 lime
* 1 carrot
* 1 cucumber
* 1/2 cup water
* 1/2 cup rice wine vinegar
* 2 tbsp. sugar
* 1/2 cup mayonnaise
* 2 tbsp. sirracha sauce
* bunch of cilantro
* 1 baguette
* 1 jalepeno, finely sliced

## Directions
* Combine the rice wine vinegar, water and sugar into a bowl and mix until sugar is dissolved
* Half the cucumber and use a spoon to scoop out the seedy middle bit
* Cut the cucumber into matchstick-sized pieces and place into the vinegar mixture
* Cut the carrot into matchstick-sized pieces and place into the vinegar mixture
* Place the bowl into a fridge for at least an hour
* Butterfly the chicken breasts and place into a bowl with the soy sauce, fish sauce and garlic
* Place chicken in a fridge for at least an hour
* Fry chicken in a hot pan until cooked through, then take out to rest
* Turn broiler on max
* Combine mayonnaise and sirracha sauce
* Halve and toast the baguette under a broiler for a minute until toasted
* Slice the chicken breast
* Spread both halves of the baguette with the mayo mix, then top with chicken, pickled vegetables, cilantro and jalapeno slices

ENJOY!


